1
00:00:01,420 --> 00:00:02,420
Ah...

2
00:00:03,130 --> 00:00:04,870
I really don't want to go back.

3
00:00:07,270 --> 00:00:08,770
Want to stay another night?

4
00:00:11,360 --> 00:00:13,380
You know I have class tonight.

5
00:00:20,360 --> 00:00:22,480
I feel like I've just been
running around in circles.

6
00:00:23,680 --> 00:00:26,489
I kept telling myself I'd take a
real break when things settled down.

7
00:00:29,090 --> 00:00:30,630
But "settling down"...

8
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:32,900
if you don't force
yourself to take the time,

9
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:35,230
it feels like it'll never happen.

10
00:00:37,770 --> 00:00:38,930
I know what you mean.

11
00:00:42,560 --> 00:00:45,910
So I'm really glad we could come.

12
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:51,810
Thanks.

13
00:00:53,380 --> 00:00:54,380
Yeah.

14
00:00:59,190 --> 00:01:01,060
This time yesterday,

15
00:01:01,880 --> 00:01:05,540
I never would have dreamed
I'd be at a hot spring today.

16
00:01:06,130 --> 00:01:10,400
You really never know
what life has in store.

17
00:01:23,740 --> 00:01:25,280
The breeze feels nice.

18
00:01:36,760 --> 00:01:37,890
What is it?

19
00:01:42,100 --> 00:01:43,270
Nothing.

20
00:01:45,970 --> 00:01:47,300
You're being weird.

21
00:01:57,810 --> 00:02:01,050
I know I'll remember this moment
countless times in the future.

22
00:02:03,380 --> 00:02:07,090
The number of days I never
want to forget keeps growing.

23
00:02:45,500 --> 00:02:50,800
"Life In Smokey Blue"

24
00:02:53,140 --> 00:02:55,340
(Final Episode: And On It Goes)
Oh, that smells amazing.

25
00:02:55,780 --> 00:02:57,670
Today's furikake is the fancy kind.

26
00:02:57,920 --> 00:02:59,480
I went to a hot spring recently.

27
00:02:59,510 --> 00:03:01,240
Oh, a hot spring? That's nice.

28
00:03:01,540 --> 00:03:02,540
Did you go by yourself?

29
00:03:02,541 --> 00:03:04,110
No, it was sort of a date.

30
00:03:04,650 --> 00:03:05,736
Oh, so you have a girlfriend.

31
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:07,260
No, a boyfriend.

32
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:09,960
Oh, my apologies.

33
00:03:10,650 --> 00:03:11,650
Not at all.

34
00:03:14,560 --> 00:03:16,490
- Shimada-san.
- Yes?

35
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:17,629
Do you have a moment?

36
00:03:17,630 --> 00:03:19,819
Yes, of course.
I'll be on my way, then.

37
00:03:19,820 --> 00:03:20,860
Okay.

38
00:03:21,900 --> 00:03:25,270
- I'm not sure I want to join...
- Huh? You're not joining?

39
00:03:27,780 --> 00:03:29,460
That really threw her for a loop.

40
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:34,610
Coming out is so hard.

41
00:03:47,100 --> 00:03:48,260
Huh?

42
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:52,920
Yeah.

43
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,400
Isn't it great?

44
00:03:55,440 --> 00:03:56,840
I think this essay is excellent.

45
00:03:58,640 --> 00:04:00,220
That's a relief.

46
00:04:00,470 --> 00:04:01,840
This is rare.

47
00:04:02,140 --> 00:04:03,780
Seeing you this nervous.

48
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:05,710
I'm more than nervous. I'm a wreck.

49
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:09,080
In the end,

50
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:11,300
you focused on him as a mentor.

51
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:16,390
I had to think about what connected
my father and me.

52
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:19,160
That makes sense.

53
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:21,269
While I was writing,

54
00:04:21,270 --> 00:04:23,690
those years I lived with my father,

55
00:04:24,030 --> 00:04:25,350
and everything I learned there...

56
00:04:26,033 --> 00:04:28,113
I feel like I was able to
sort through it all again.

57
00:04:30,370 --> 00:04:31,370
Although,

58
00:04:31,870 --> 00:04:34,900
I did a lot of complaining and agonizing
before I could even start writing.

59
00:04:37,220 --> 00:04:38,700
You worked hard on it.

60
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:42,560
Ah.

61
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:45,940
The hot spring was amazing.

62
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:49,180
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you.

63
00:04:49,759 --> 00:04:51,959
You really didn't have to.

64
00:04:52,020 --> 00:04:53,920
Oh, furikake.

65
00:04:54,640 --> 00:04:56,090
That one is really good.

66
00:04:59,620 --> 00:05:01,700
Shizuka-chan, you have a
great expression right now.

67
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:06,900
Thanks.

68
00:05:16,500 --> 00:05:18,180
I'm always reminded,

69
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:22,920
of the little things from those days.

70
00:05:29,761 --> 00:05:31,574
[Overview of actual
sales, monthly breakdown]

71
00:05:35,700 --> 00:05:37,640
Chasing after numbers and deadlines,

72
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:45,170
the people behind this work...

73
00:05:45,380 --> 00:05:46,540
Are you all right?

74
00:05:46,910 --> 00:05:49,510
- Take your time. There's no rush.
- I was about to overlook it.

75
00:05:51,500 --> 00:05:52,710
Oh, Kuji-san.

76
00:06:01,540 --> 00:06:03,160
About the new case report,

77
00:06:03,190 --> 00:06:05,230
I'll send you a separate email.

78
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:06,700
That would be a great help.

79
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:09,630
Thank you so much for today.

80
00:06:15,780 --> 00:06:18,599
Oh, isn't it your daughter's
coming-of-age ceremony soon?

81
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:19,800
Yes, it is.

82
00:06:20,080 --> 00:06:23,010
She's so excited about everything,
from the kimono to her hair.

83
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:25,179
Congratulations.

84
00:06:25,180 --> 00:06:26,180
Thank you.

85
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:28,040
Well, I'll be going.

86
00:06:30,170 --> 00:06:31,250
Kuji-san.

87
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:34,990
Are you okay?

88
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:36,930
Aren't you tired?

89
00:06:40,940 --> 00:06:41,940
No.

90
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:43,500
I'm fine.

91
00:06:45,740 --> 00:06:46,740
That's good.

92
00:06:47,380 --> 00:06:48,580
But don't overdo it.

93
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:51,670
Okay.

94
00:06:54,010 --> 00:06:55,110
Excuse me.

95
00:06:58,910 --> 00:07:00,250
Good work.

96
00:07:01,340 --> 00:07:02,459
I'll get it.

97
00:07:02,460 --> 00:07:03,460
It's fine.

98
00:07:03,461 --> 00:07:04,820
I used it too, after all.

99
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:08,620
Back then, I thought he
was a fascinating man.

100
00:07:10,940 --> 00:07:13,100
A strength that never boasted,
no matter who he faced,

101
00:07:14,660 --> 00:07:16,430
and a kindness he never tried to hide.

102
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:28,000
(Incoming Call: Kimitsu Clinic)

103
00:07:28,380 --> 00:07:29,610
Hello, Kuji speaking.

104
00:07:31,660 --> 00:07:32,680
Yes.

105
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:35,520
What?

106
00:07:38,260 --> 00:07:39,460
Dr. Kimitsu...

107
00:07:55,580 --> 00:07:56,840
Are you okay?

108
00:08:00,580 --> 00:08:01,740
What?

109
00:08:14,060 --> 00:08:15,860
Unable to simply accept someone's kindness,

110
00:08:16,920 --> 00:08:19,090
and feeling pathetic for my own weakness.

111
00:08:22,280 --> 00:08:23,260
Hey, listen to this.

112
00:08:23,261 --> 00:08:25,360
Dr. Fujiwara was talking about golf today.

113
00:08:25,460 --> 00:08:27,960
"If you've got the energy,
don't hesitate, just swing!"

114
00:08:28,460 --> 00:08:30,710
- He yelled, "Hah!"
- No way.

115
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:32,500
- You're exaggerating.
- I'm serious.

116
00:08:33,660 --> 00:08:35,310
I wanted to be like Azuma.

117
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:40,080
Was this feeling... admiration?

118
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:46,400
No.

119
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:48,720
It was more than that.

120
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:52,360
This feeling was...

121
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:02,300
(Azuma Sakutaro)

122
00:09:04,940 --> 00:09:05,940
Kuji.

123
00:09:19,980 --> 00:09:21,360
- Drink up.
- Yeah.

124
00:09:27,780 --> 00:09:29,060
Did someone stop by?

125
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:32,820
Oh, that was Nukita-san.

126
00:09:33,860 --> 00:09:35,540
I had him take a look at
the essay I wrote.

127
00:09:35,660 --> 00:09:36,660
Oh.

128
00:09:37,560 --> 00:09:38,770
You finished it?

129
00:09:40,040 --> 00:09:41,140
Yeah, more or less.

130
00:09:42,380 --> 00:09:44,210
Nukita-san gave it pretty good feedback.

131
00:09:48,620 --> 00:09:49,620
That's great.

132
00:09:50,190 --> 00:09:51,190
Yeah.

133
00:09:59,460 --> 00:10:00,560
Did something happen?

134
00:10:09,020 --> 00:10:11,840
The results of the translation
competition are out.

135
00:10:13,940 --> 00:10:15,180
I won a special prize.

136
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:18,350
It's the third-place prize.

137
00:10:19,980 --> 00:10:20,980
Oh!

138
00:10:22,420 --> 00:10:23,420
Congratulations.

139
00:10:24,450 --> 00:10:25,450
Thanks.

140
00:10:26,420 --> 00:10:27,520
I'm happy, but...

141
00:10:28,390 --> 00:10:29,860
I'm also frustrated.

142
00:10:31,280 --> 00:10:33,700
I feel like I could have done better.

143
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:38,729
I feel like I'm just shameless.
I don't have the skill,

144
00:10:38,730 --> 00:10:40,040
but I act like I do.

145
00:10:41,700 --> 00:10:42,500
At this rate,

146
00:10:42,501 --> 00:10:45,140
can I really make a career out of this?

147
00:10:48,210 --> 00:10:49,410
I'm the same way.

148
00:10:50,980 --> 00:10:53,450
I've always been stuck in a cycle
of arrogance and regret.

149
00:10:55,740 --> 00:10:56,960
Even you, Kuji-san?

150
00:10:59,320 --> 00:11:01,390
Even Kuji-san goes through it.

151
00:11:03,980 --> 00:11:07,360
I never realized you were working
under so much pressure and tension.

152
00:11:08,340 --> 00:11:09,340
Kuji-san.

153
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:11,600
You're so cool.

154
00:11:12,770 --> 00:11:13,770
I know, right?

155
00:11:14,540 --> 00:11:16,170
What are you so smug about?

156
00:11:16,270 --> 00:11:17,340
Ow.

157
00:11:23,900 --> 00:11:25,580
It really is important to talk things out.

158
00:11:26,940 --> 00:11:28,180
I feel so much lighter.

159
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:32,420
I'm glad to hear that.

160
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:38,100
That's tight.

161
00:11:38,160 --> 00:11:39,580
Hey, it's too tight.

162
00:11:40,180 --> 00:11:41,260
Okay, okay.

163
00:11:47,620 --> 00:11:49,610
I should probably get going.

164
00:11:51,270 --> 00:11:52,540
I have papers to grade.

165
00:11:57,110 --> 00:11:58,350
Want me to walk you home?

166
00:11:58,460 --> 00:11:59,750
No, no, it's fine.

167
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:05,420
You've already carried me,
held me, and slept with me.

168
00:12:05,490 --> 00:12:07,090
I'd be taking too much
of an advantage of you.

169
00:12:07,260 --> 00:12:08,700
What's wrong with sleeping together?

170
00:12:12,590 --> 00:12:16,570
Hey, you forgot your kiss.

171
00:12:42,170 --> 00:12:43,970
You know, maybe I
shouldn't go home just yet.

172
00:12:46,110 --> 00:12:47,110
Okay.

173
00:12:54,910 --> 00:12:56,000
That day...

174
00:12:56,870 --> 00:12:58,410
The territory I was in charge of...

175
00:12:59,190 --> 00:13:00,410
You're taking it over, right?

176
00:13:01,670 --> 00:13:03,650
I'll teach you the ropes
of dealing with doctors.

177
00:13:06,480 --> 00:13:07,480
Okay.

178
00:13:13,870 --> 00:13:16,830
I'd never seen him make that face before.

179
00:13:18,190 --> 00:13:21,030
I just found it so endearing.

180
00:13:22,350 --> 00:13:27,440
That night was both a beginning and an end.
I thought that was all it would be.

181
00:13:40,590 --> 00:13:42,190
I wanted to see his face one last time,

182
00:13:46,130 --> 00:13:47,620
but I stopped myself.

183
00:13:51,030 --> 00:13:52,590
Because if I looked at his face,

184
00:13:54,230 --> 00:13:56,530
I felt like I wouldn't
be able to walk away.

185
00:14:01,390 --> 00:14:02,640
We hold each other.

186
00:14:04,670 --> 00:14:06,040
Share our warmth.

187
00:14:08,430 --> 00:14:11,750
Share the pain, and share the joy.

188
00:14:14,050 --> 00:14:15,550
What are you thinking about?

189
00:14:17,990 --> 00:14:20,560
I'm thinking I want to
tell myself from back then.

190
00:14:22,330 --> 00:14:23,330
Tell him what?

191
00:14:32,590 --> 00:14:33,729
Thanks to your guidance,

192
00:14:33,730 --> 00:14:36,270
I won a special prize in the competition.

193
00:14:36,950 --> 00:14:37,950
I see.

194
00:14:38,870 --> 00:14:40,280
I, on the other hand, didn't place.

195
00:14:41,730 --> 00:14:42,940
I'm very sorry.

196
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:46,250
That's nothing to apologize for.

197
00:14:46,910 --> 00:14:49,150
Competitions are also a matter of fate.

198
00:14:50,450 --> 00:14:51,450
Right...

199
00:14:56,450 --> 00:14:58,969
You both look pretty disappointed.

200
00:14:58,970 --> 00:14:59,970
No...

201
00:15:03,510 --> 00:15:04,510
Yes.

202
00:15:05,750 --> 00:15:06,840
I'm so frustrated.

203
00:15:07,930 --> 00:15:09,040
I can't accept it.

204
00:15:11,640 --> 00:15:12,640
Me too.

205
00:15:14,990 --> 00:15:17,450
Translation isn't about rankings.

206
00:15:18,110 --> 00:15:21,280
It's about conveying the
author's voice to the reader.

207
00:15:22,670 --> 00:15:26,490
I believe you both have that power.

208
00:15:31,870 --> 00:15:33,830
Thank you so much.

209
00:15:36,550 --> 00:15:40,040
So, there's something I'd
like to discuss with you both.

210
00:15:43,970 --> 00:15:45,070
A first-draft translation?

211
00:15:46,110 --> 00:15:47,110
What's that?

212
00:15:48,030 --> 00:15:49,030
Well...

213
00:15:49,430 --> 00:15:53,450
It's sort of like being an
assistant for the lead translator.

214
00:15:55,150 --> 00:15:56,620
Isn't that amazing?

215
00:15:56,950 --> 00:15:59,350
You've already landed a translation job.

216
00:16:01,070 --> 00:16:03,660
Well, I guess you could call it a job.

217
00:16:05,490 --> 00:16:06,660
I'm really grateful.

218
00:16:07,390 --> 00:16:08,390
Yeah.

219
00:16:08,530 --> 00:16:09,810
You have to thank them properly.

220
00:16:11,270 --> 00:16:12,270
You're right.

221
00:16:13,830 --> 00:16:15,940
Mom, how have you been feeling lately?

222
00:16:17,050 --> 00:16:18,050
Hmm...

223
00:16:18,850 --> 00:16:21,440
Some good days, some bad.

224
00:16:22,730 --> 00:16:24,650
But, well, that's just how it is.

225
00:16:25,270 --> 00:16:26,980
That's all you can ask for in life.

226
00:16:29,290 --> 00:16:30,290
I see.

227
00:16:32,110 --> 00:16:36,020
By the way, I went to that rose garden.

228
00:16:36,310 --> 00:16:38,560
It was absolutely beautiful.

229
00:16:43,300 --> 00:16:44,470
What's wrong?

230
00:16:45,250 --> 00:16:46,250
It's nothing.

231
00:16:47,490 --> 00:16:49,170
I'll be back again soon.

232
00:16:49,650 --> 00:16:50,650
Okay.

233
00:16:51,730 --> 00:16:52,870
I'll be waiting.

234
00:17:08,660 --> 00:17:09,890
What's bothering you?

235
00:17:10,990 --> 00:17:11,990
No, no.

236
00:17:12,430 --> 00:17:14,500
I want to try and figure
it out on my own first.

237
00:17:15,410 --> 00:17:16,510
Fair enough.

238
00:17:16,830 --> 00:17:18,300
- Sorry.
- Yeah.

239
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:22,040
Oh.

240
00:17:24,970 --> 00:17:27,190
Oh... Sorry, sorry.

241
00:17:27,730 --> 00:17:28,930
I just remembered something.

242
00:17:29,490 --> 00:17:30,886
When I was translating "Song of Spring"...

243
00:17:30,910 --> 00:17:32,480
Kuji, you taught me, didn't you?

244
00:17:32,950 --> 00:17:36,020
You said, "Try to avoid
translating in the first person."

245
00:17:36,830 --> 00:17:37,830
Oh, right.

246
00:17:41,490 --> 00:17:44,060
I think that approach
might work for this one, too.

247
00:17:45,930 --> 00:17:47,230
That makes sense.

248
00:18:00,510 --> 00:18:01,510
Azuma.

249
00:18:01,540 --> 00:18:02,540
Hmm?

250
00:18:09,220 --> 00:18:10,220
Here.

251
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:14,920
What?

252
00:18:15,430 --> 00:18:16,630
The key to this house.

253
00:18:18,230 --> 00:18:19,230
Huh?

254
00:18:21,460 --> 00:18:22,560
Is this a proposal?

255
00:18:23,970 --> 00:18:25,930
Call it what you want.

256
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:30,340
Ooh.

257
00:18:42,660 --> 00:18:45,950
Oh, but when you come over,
be sure to let me know first.

258
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:47,920
Okay.

259
00:19:02,720 --> 00:19:06,280
- Tamaki, congratulations on getting into college.
- Thanks.

260
00:19:06,310 --> 00:19:08,080
Cheers.

261
00:19:11,680 --> 00:19:13,939
Sorry this celebration is so late.

262
00:19:13,940 --> 00:19:14,940
Not at all.

263
00:19:14,980 --> 00:19:16,420
I've been busy anyway.

264
00:19:17,390 --> 00:19:19,166
Congratulations on
graduating high school, too.

265
00:19:19,190 --> 00:19:20,220
Thanks.

266
00:19:21,660 --> 00:19:22,660
Oh, right.

267
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:23,960
Let's take a picture.

268
00:19:24,440 --> 00:19:25,960
- The three of us together.
- Okay.

269
00:19:30,280 --> 00:19:31,800
Okay, smile.

270
00:19:37,380 --> 00:19:38,380
Nice.

271
00:19:39,600 --> 00:19:41,729
I told Grandma about today.

272
00:19:41,730 --> 00:19:43,280
She asked me to send her the picture.

273
00:19:43,660 --> 00:19:46,210
Oh, you're going to
Yamanashi next week, right?

274
00:19:47,220 --> 00:19:48,250
Really?

275
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:50,050
Is Kuji-san going with you?

276
00:19:51,720 --> 00:19:53,020
I'm not going.

277
00:19:54,540 --> 00:19:56,430
Oh, I see.

278
00:19:56,460 --> 00:19:57,490
Right.

279
00:19:58,120 --> 00:19:59,530
Sorry, that was a weird question.

280
00:20:07,560 --> 00:20:09,040
Um, Tamaki.

281
00:20:10,220 --> 00:20:11,220
Yeah?

282
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:15,910
Kuji and I are a couple.

283
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:20,250
I'm sure you've probably already noticed.

284
00:20:22,780 --> 00:20:26,220
But I don't plan on telling my grandmother.

285
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:30,430
So I don't think our families
will be interacting in the future.

286
00:20:33,340 --> 00:20:34,340
Okay.

287
00:20:34,920 --> 00:20:36,000
I understand.

288
00:20:37,780 --> 00:20:38,980
Sorry to spring this on you.

289
00:20:39,880 --> 00:20:42,470
I just wanted to tell you the simple truth.

290
00:20:43,840 --> 00:20:45,840
Just thought you should know.

291
00:20:50,380 --> 00:20:51,380
Huh?

292
00:20:53,720 --> 00:20:54,820
I feel like...

293
00:20:56,940 --> 00:20:58,690
How do I put this...

294
00:21:02,290 --> 00:21:04,170
Part of me is nervous
and my heart is pounding,

295
00:21:05,700 --> 00:21:07,500
but another part of me is relieved.

296
00:21:11,780 --> 00:21:13,970
I can't really explain the feeling myself.

297
00:21:20,700 --> 00:21:21,700
But...

298
00:21:24,300 --> 00:21:26,750
I've always hoped you
two would be like this.

299
00:21:34,360 --> 00:21:35,540
Tamaki...

300
00:21:43,060 --> 00:21:44,460
Kuji?!

301
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:47,370
What are you two doing?

302
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:51,780
What the heck?

303
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:53,410
Seriously, what's with you two?

304
00:21:53,580 --> 00:21:54,640
Shut up.

305
00:22:02,220 --> 00:22:03,420
My eyes hurt...

306
00:22:04,680 --> 00:22:06,240
That's what you get for crying so much.

307
00:22:09,560 --> 00:22:11,590
It's been a year and a half since then.

308
00:22:13,160 --> 00:22:14,100
Since then?

309
00:22:14,160 --> 00:22:15,260
You know.

310
00:22:15,280 --> 00:22:16,770
At the bar, you... to me...

311
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:18,440
Hey.

312
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:20,600
Where are you trying to take him?

313
00:22:25,980 --> 00:22:26,980
Yeah.

314
00:22:27,920 --> 00:22:29,300
Don't you act all innocent.

315
00:22:29,310 --> 00:22:30,780
Stop it.

316
00:22:31,080 --> 00:22:32,210
Oh.

317
00:22:33,650 --> 00:22:35,020
It's a dogwood tree.

318
00:22:38,640 --> 00:22:40,560
It blooms in the yard every spring.

319
00:22:41,740 --> 00:22:42,740
Oh, right.

320
00:22:43,460 --> 00:22:44,760
Those are the flower buds.

321
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:51,770
Let's go back.

322
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:53,600
Okay.

323
00:23:02,510 --> 00:23:03,880
You're heavy.

324
00:23:04,280 --> 00:23:05,810
You can feel spring in the air.

325
00:23:06,940 --> 00:23:07,940
You're really heavy.

326
00:23:09,320 --> 00:23:12,020
And days like these
will continue on and on.
